legacy.full_text: From Long March rockets🚀 to Chang'e lunar projects🌕,  from Tiangong space station 🛰️ to Tianwen-1 Mars mission, I have witnessed dozens of key space missions and programs in China over the past years. Those astonishing and breathtaking moments are always lingering in mind. https://t.co/4ZdL5Wgr8F

legacy.full_text:
All #Shenzhou16 crew members exited the capsule safely at 9:10 a.m. BJT on Tuesday. 
As of now, taikonaut #JingHaipeng has successfully completed his 4th space flight, becoming the Chinese astronaut who performed the most missions. His cumulative time in space surpassed 200 days. https://t.co/6DWINMrPG7

legacy.full_text:
The re-entry capsule touched down at the #Dongfeng landing site in north China at 8:11 a.m. BJT on Tuesday.

Medical personnel confirmed that all three taikonauts are in good health. #CMSA announced the #Shenzhou16 manned spaceflight mission was a complete success. https://t.co/WiMgPxZhIA

legacy.full_text:
Touchdown! The #Shenzhou16 taikonauts have returned to Earth safely after 5-month mission on Tiangong.

The re-entry capsule with 3 taikonauts aboard – Jing Haipeng, Zhu Yangzhu & Gui Haichao – touched down at the Dongfeng landing site in north China on Tuesday morning. https://t.co/FNaSvJpjKl

#Shenzhou16 crew, thank you for your hard work!
#Shenzhou17 crew, wish everything go well during your stay in orbit!
An in-orbit handover ceremony was held at #Tiangong on Sunday. The Shenzhou-16 crew will return to Earth tomorrow. https://t.co/UnJXO2DU6I

legacy.full_text:
#Dongfeng landing site is ready!
Over 10 search and rescue groups, 5 #helicopters & nearly 100 #vehicles participated in the final drills recently.
Based on estimation of the landing time, the air unit will get prepared and take off at dawn. #Shenzhou16return
Photo : CMSA/CFP https://t.co/nPPcSuaNsc

The #Shenzhou16 and #Shenzhou17 completed in-orbit handover on Sunday.

The Shenzhou-16 astronaut crew has completed all scheduled tasks and will return to the #Dongfeng Landing Site on October 31. https://t.co/Q51o3AS7Rp

legacy.full_text:
A team led by scientists from #ChineseAcademyofSciences revealed the origin & implication of #pentlandite in #Change5 lunar soils, through transmission electron microscopy analyses. 

This provides new clues for exploring the origin & geological evolution of sulfides on the Moon. https://t.co/xXUOOkPQQC

legacy.full_text:
The #Dongfeng landing site near Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center is gearing up for the return of the #Shenzhou16 crew.
The Shenzhou-16 trio will come back to Earth on Oct.31, after spending about 5 months in space. https://t.co/5YGc7bstlE

legacy.full_text:
Watch the breathtaking footage of #Shenzhou17 spacecraft docking with the #Tiangong space station.

The spaceship docked with the front port of the space station's #Tianhe core module at 5:46 p.m.Beijing time on Thursday, 6.5 hours later after its blastoff. https://t.co/i3Mivy1AAr

legacy.description: 🚀Space Journalist🚀 Covering astronauts, China Space station, Lunar and Mars exploration and other space explorations 🌕Personal Views 🌍

legacy.full_text:
A warm hug in space!
The #Shenzhou16 crew opened the hatch at 19:34 BJT on Thursday, met with their colleagues — the #Shenzhou17 crew at China Space Station.
The 6 taikonauts will live and work together for about 4 days to complete planned tasks & handover work.
（Photo:#CMSA) https://t.co/hhRTP7YA2q

legacy.full_text: A successful dock！After about 6.5 hours, the #Shenzhou17 spacecraft docked with the front port of the #Tiangong space station‘s Tianhe core module. (Photo Credit: #CMSA) https://t.co/CwyfhPlC1Q

legacy.description: 🚀Space Journalist🚀 Covering astronauts, China Space station, Lunar and Mars exploration and other space explorations 🌕Personal Views 🌍

legacy.full_text:
The #Shenzhou17 manned spaceship has successfully docked with the front port of the #Tiangong space station‘s Tianhe core module, forming a three-module three-ship assembly. 

The whole process took about  6.5 hours.
Three taikonauts will enter Tianhe core module later. https://t.co/2KG2w0yVtt

After #Shenzhou17 mission launch, Rong Yi, the #ChiefDesigner of #China's only manned carrier rocket has passed the baton and taken on a new role.

She will work on the next generation manned carrier rocket. What would these new rockets be like? Click the video below. https://t.co/esPFV853Fz
